<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-048-014 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 179 003</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  Oct 1991 v8 n10 p154(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PC-VCR. (computer-controlled stereo VCR from NEC TechnologiesInc.) (Hardware Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pogue, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>NEC Technologies $2,100 PC-VCR is an innovativecomputer-controlled stereo VCR that offers many powerfulcapabilities.andP;  The hardware is attractive and slim and comes witha serial port that can be connected to any Macintosh.andP;  Althoughthe product offers excellent video features, includingframe-accurate search capability and stereo sound, it suffers frompoor documentation and lacks useful software.andP;  All the VCR'scontrols, such as fast-forward and rewind, can be controlled froma Mac's keyboard, but the commands can only be used by programmingthem first.andP;  Experienced HyperTalk programmers can use HyperCardto overcome this problem, but NEC provides no documentation on howto do so and gives little help when contacted.andP;  The PC-VCR is agood product, but it needs improvement in the areas ofdocumentation and support.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   NEC Technologies Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   NEC PC-VCR (Video tape player and recorder).andO;Topic:     EvaluationVideocassette RecordersPeripherals.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>